J&J Says Andrew Ekdahl to Lead DePuy Joint-Replacement Unit

-- B y   A l e x   N u s s b a u m
-- 
2011-06-13T19:59:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/j-j-says-andrew-ekdahl-to-lead-depuy-joint-replacement-unit.html
Johnson & Johnson (JNJ)  said Andrew Ekdahl
has been named president of DePuy Orthopaedics, the maker of
artificial hips and knees that has struggled with product
recalls and declining sales.  Ekdahl, a 20-year veteran at the company, was formerly
DePuy’s franchise vice president for Europe, the Middle East and
Africa, according to an e-mailed statement today from  New
Brunswick , New Jersey-based J&J.  DePuy announced the resignation of the unit’s former
president, David Floyd, in March, saying he left to pursue other
interests.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Nussbaum in New York 
